quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  43,11,"And He Who sent down water from the sky in due proportion, whereby We revived a lifeless land; thus <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">are brought out<sup foot_note=""81096"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>."
  43,12,"And He Who created all pairs and provided you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>with ships and livestock on which you ride,"
  43,13,"that you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>may mount their backs then remember the blessing of your Lord as you settle upon them and say, “Highly Exalted is the One Who has subjected this to us, and in no way could we have done it by ourselves,"
  43,14,"and indeed to our Lord we are certainly returning.”"
  43,15,"Yet they ascribed to Him a portion of His servants. Surely, man is indeed an evidently staunch denier."
  43,16,"Or has He chosen for Himself daughters from what He creates, and favored you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>with sons?"
  43,17,"Yet when one of them is given glad tidings{1}of what he ascribed to the All-Merciful, his face becomes dark as he suppresses his anguish,",footnotes:1:This is said in sarcasm.
  43,18,"<i class=""s"">(thinking) </i>“What! Someone <span class=""h"">brought up<sup foot_note=""81098"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>amid adornments and, in conflict, cannot be evident?”{2}",footnotes:2:Pagans looked at women in a demeaning way.
  43,19,"And they considered the angels, who are <span class=""h"">servants<sup foot_note=""81100"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">of</span>the All-Merciful, to be females. <span class=""h"">Did they witness<sup foot_note=""81101"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>their creation? Their claim will be recorded and they will be asked."
  43,20,"And they said, “Had the All-Merciful willed, we would not have worshiped them.” But they have no knowledge of that; they are merely conjecturing."
  43,21,"Or have We brought them a scripture prior to this one{1}, so that they are adhering to it?",footnotes:1:The Qur’an.
  43,22,"Rather, they said, “Indeed, we found our forefathers on a course{1}, and indeed we are being guided in their footsteps.”",footnotes:1:Literally ‘a nation: a community’.
